{
  "texts": [
    "DCC-MD [81] and TMC [31] use handcrafted rules to prune received messages.",
    "In DCC-MD, each received message can be dropped out with a certain probability.",
    "TMC stores the received messages and checks whether they are expired or not within a preset time window.",
    "Only valid messages are integrated into an agent's model.",
    "Instead of using fixed rules, ℜ-MACRL [66] learns a gate unit to decide whether to use a received message."
  ]
}